Implementation summary:
- Every new contract lives in the namespace VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Abstractions
  and ships from the existing VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Abstractions.asmdef
  (no new asmdef created). The asmdef retains noEngineReferences=true and
  references=[], so the abstraction layer remains free of Unity- and
  concrete-implementation dependencies.
- ICoreIpcBus matches design.md §"Service Interface" for CoreIpcBus exactly,
  including Action<TPayload> handlers, the
  Func<TRequest, CancellationToken, Task<TResponse>> request-handler shape,
  and IConnectionDiagnostics Diagnostics property.
- ICoreIpcRuntime extends IDisposable per design.md §"Service Interface" for
  CoreIpcRuntime, exposes the live RuntimeState defined in task 1.3, and the
  CoreIpcOptions defined in task 1.2.
- ITransportAdapter / IClientConnection match design.md §"Service Interface"
  for WebSocketTransportAdapter and adopt IAsyncDisposable for symmetric
  resource release. ReceiveAsync returns
  IAsyncEnumerable<ReadOnlyMemory<byte>> so adapters can yield raw text
  frame payloads without forcing an array allocation per frame.
- IMessageCodec returns IpcResult<T> rather than throwing, matching the
  "失敗時は InvalidEnvelope エラー" rule from Req 3.5 and design.md §3.5.
- IConnectionDiagnostics + DiagnosticsSnapshot match design.md §"#### CoreIpcDiagnostics"
  one-for-one. ConnectionStateChanged uses Action<ConnectionState, ConnectionState>
  (previous, current) per design.md §"##### Event Contract" of
  ConnectionStateMachine.
- IAuthenticationHandler is intentionally minimal (Req 6.6 "拡張余地"):
  one async method that receives RemoteEndpoint / Origin /
  AuthorizationHeader so a future WebUI / LAN deployment can plug in
  Origin-header validation or token-based auth without breaking the
  abstraction surface.
- RequestOptions is filed under Runtime/Abstractions/Results/ alongside
  IpcResult per the source-tree layout in design.md §"Source Files Layout".

